### 3. Data Exposure Prevention

- [ ] No sensitive data in log output (passwords, tokens, PII)
- [ ] API responses don't leak internal data (stack traces, DB schemas)
- [ ] Error messages are generic for external users, detailed for internal logs
- [ ] Sensitive fields are masked in any debugging output

